      • parseModule

        public static ModuleNode parseModule(Object obj)
                              throws Parser.ParseException
        Parse a ModuleNode from a parsed s-expression as obtained from Reader.readAll(CharSequence).

        Note that this does not validate the module, but will fail if the module is syntactically incorrect.

        Parameters:
        obj - The read s-expression representation of the module.
        Returns:
        The parsed ModuleNode.
        Throws:
        Parser.ParseException - If obj is not a syntactically valid module.

      • parseBinaryModule

        public static ModuleNode parseBinaryModule(Object obj)
                                    throws Parser.ParseException
        Parse a ModuleNode from a module written as (module id? binary ...), which may appear in WAST scripts.

        Much like parseModule(Object), this does not validate the modules.

        Parameters:
        obj - The read s-expression representation of the module.
        Returns:
        The parsed ModuleNode.
        Throws:
        Parser.ParseException - If obj is not a syntactically valid module.

        Much like parseModule(Object), this does not validate the modules.

        Returns:
